attachAsNew

public static void attachAsNew(AlphaTranlocal tranlocal)
Attaches a Tranlocal to a transaction. The transaction is retrieved from the ThreadLocalTransaction. If no transaction is found, a RuntimeException is thrown.

This method is called by instrumented atomicobjects.

Parameters:
tranlocal - the AlphaTranlocal to attach.

isAttached

public static boolean isAttached(AlphaAtomicObject atomicObject)
Checks if there already is a tranlocal attached for the atomicobject.

This method is called by instrumented atomicobjects.

Parameters:
atomicObject - the AtomicObject to check
Returns:
true if the atomicObject is attached, false otherwise.

load

public static AlphaTranlocal load(Object atomicObject)
Loads a Tranlocal using a transaction. The transaction is retrieved from the ThreadLocalTransaction. If no transaction is found, a RuntimeException is thrown.

For more information see AlphaTransaction.load(AlphaAtomicObject)

This method is called by instrumented atomicobjects.

Parameters:
atomicObject - the AlphaAtomicObject.
Returns:
the AlphaTranlocal
